- There are two methods handling that path in the source: both are annotated with @POST (one @Consumes("application/json"), the other @Consumes({"application/yaml","text/yaml"})). They are annotated @Hidden (to exclude them from automatic OpenAPI generation) but they are present in the code and both accept POST requests with different Content-Types. Thus POST is accepted.

- The provided openapi-configuration.json also documents /api/v0/lifecycle/configure with a POST operation, which matches the source.
